/use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 10, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104evi1665702596474.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/evi1665702596474.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/evi1665702596474.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"evi1665702596474\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"evi1665702596474__apisgl_functions_401087\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Unless otherwise indicated, all 3GL functions are available on all\n      platforms.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"evi1665702596474__p_d118640e1_d118641e1_d118642e1\">In the 3GL function descriptions, note the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"evi1665702596474__li_d45029e1_d45030e1_d45031e1\">All Uniface 3GL functions have lowercase names, as\n            do most of the symbols in the shared libraries. However, there are some exceptions. <p class=\"p\" id=\"evi1665702596474__p_d118643e1_d118644e1_d118645e1\">The include file <span class=\"ph filepath\">h3gl.h</span>\n               maps the lowercase names to uppercase or to mixed-case, if necessary. We recommend\n               that you always include <span class=\"ph filepath\">h3gl.h</span>, and call functions using only\n               their lowercase names. If you do not include <span class=\"ph filepath\">h3gl.h</span>, you might\n               get unresolved externals when you link in the shared library.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"evi1665702596474__li_d45032e1_d45033e1_d45034e1\">String parameters for the functions, input or\n            output, are always zero-terminated, C style, and passed by reference as a pointer,\n            unless otherwise noted. <p class=\"p\" id=\"evi1665702596474__p_d118646e1_d118647e1_d118648e1\">Instead of saying the\n               precisely correct, <var class=\"keyword varname\">format</var>—a pointer to a zero-terminated character\n               string containing the format, we simply say: <var class=\"keyword varname\">format</var>—a string\n               containing the format, or the format..</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"evi1665702596474__li_d45035e1_d45036e1_d45037e1\">For brevity, most of the examples shown omit the\n            checking of return codes. Always check against all possible documented values, and take\n            the applicable action. This is a good programming practice, which we strongly\n            endorse.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"evi1665702596474__note_N10055_N10016_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Functions that are not mentioned in this reference material are not supported and should not be used.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"evi1665702596474__p_d118655e1_d118656e1_d118657e1\">A number of Uniface 3GL functions were documented in\n         previous versions of Uniface, but are now obsolete. These functions are listed in the\n         \"Obsolete 3GL Functions\" topic. Some of these functions are mentioned in the include files\n         that we distribute in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">include</span> directory of your Uniface\n         installation. However, this does not imply that you can use them.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hhd1665702596552.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Obsolete 3GL Functions</a><p>Some Uniface 3GL functions that were previously available or documented are obsolete.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527345\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527345\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "APIs: 3GL Functions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 10, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Unless otherwise indicated, all 3GL functions are available on all platforms. In the 3GL function descriptions, note the following: All Uniface 3GL functions have lowercase names, as do most of the symbols in the shared libraries. However, there are some exceptions. The include file h3gl.h maps the lowercase names to uppercase or to mixed-case, if necessary. We recommend that you always include h3gl.h , and call functions using only their lowercase names. If you do not include h3gl.h , you might get unresolved externals when you link in the shared library. String parameters for the functions, input or output, are always zero-terminated, C style, and passed by reference as a pointer, unless otherwise noted. Instead of saying the precisely correct, format —a pointer to a zero-terminated character string containing the format, we simply say: format —a string containing the format, or the format.. For brevity, most of the examples shown omit the checking of return codes. Always check against all possible documented values, and take the applicable action. This is a good programming practice, which we strongly endorse. Note: Functions that are not mentioned in this reference material are not supported and should not be used. A number of Uniface 3GL functions were documented in previous versions of Uniface, but are now obsolete. These functions are listed in the \"Obsolete 3GL Functions\" topic. Some of these functions are mentioned in the include files that we distribute in the include directory of your Uniface installation. However, this does not imply that you can use them. Related Links Obsolete 3GL Functions Some Uniface 3GL functions that were previously available or documented are obsolete. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}